Female genitalia (Fig. 22
A-E
): tignum long, narrow, slightly bent, with central canal; anterior sclerotization relatively wide, posterior sclerotization well delineated, narrower than anterior (Fig. 22A). Vaginal palpi elongate, basally strongly sclerotized, each with eight setae at apex. Palpi narrowly rounded at apex, posterior sclerotization slightly curved on side (Fig. 22B), separated on more than one third of their length (Fig. 22B). Spermatheca curved, with receptacle and pump not differentiated from each other, receptacle longer than pump. Apex of pump with relatively thick spoon-like projection. Spermathecal duct short, widest at base, without coils, making narrow loop (Fig. 22C).
